{"TopicId":33124,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.11.x] RCS Build Aid v1.0.6","CreatedByName":"m4v","CreatedById":67965,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-06-15T15:58:50Z","PageNum":36,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-22T01:21:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n@Foxster\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n@Aelfhe1m\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n@Gordon Dry\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n@billkerbinsky\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113764-foxster/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022113764\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113764-foxster/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Foxster\u003C/a\u003E, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/142910-aelfhe1m/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022142910\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/142910-aelfhe1m/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Aelfhe1m\u003C/a\u003E, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/163177-gordon-dry/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022163177\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/163177-gordon-dry/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Gordon Dry\u003C/a\u003E, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/136995-billkerbinsky/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022136995\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/136995-billkerbinsky/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@billkerbinsky\u003C/a\u003E \u00A0new version is available\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aelfhe1m","CreatedById":142910,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-22T01:46:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223099311\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002233124\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221498092672\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n52 minutes ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk. \u00A0Try this, please:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/d1u3jstepbd8gbd/RCSBuildAidSkinFixBeta3.zip?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.dropbox.com/s/d1u3jstepbd8gbd/RCSBuildAidSkinFixBeta3.zip?dl=0\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, and before someone complains, my github repo has the latest changes\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust tested this in my many mod game and looks good. The usual steps I was using to create a display glitch are no longer a problem.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSteps that used to cause a glitch:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nput craft in eccentric orbit around Kerbin\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nset moon as target\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nopen manoeuvre planner window in MechJeb\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nselect \u0022Hohmann transfer to target\u0022 from dropdown and click \u0022Create node\u0022 button\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nlarge block of warning text is displayed that should wrap onto several lines but wasn\u0027t in bugged version\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-22T01:48:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGreat, will get a new release file out.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks \u00A0for testing\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-22T02:00:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNew unofficial release, 0.9.1.2:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nFixes issue where mod messes up other mod windows\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/linuxgurugamer/RCSBuildAid/releases/tag/0.9.1.2\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/linuxgurugamer/RCSBuildAid/releases/tag/0.9.1.2\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Foxster","CreatedById":113764,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-22T06:32:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMany thanks, LGG.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat seems to have done the job.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"selfish_meme","CreatedById":125899,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-22T10:12:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223099345\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002233124\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221498096833\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNew unofficial release, 0.9.1.2:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nFixes issue where mod messes up other mod windows\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/linuxgurugamer/RCSBuildAid/releases/tag/0.9.1.2\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/linuxgurugamer/RCSBuildAid/releases/tag/0.9.1.2\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave you got a Patreon page or something LGG?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-22T10:53:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223099586\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002233124\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221498126363\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022125899\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022selfish_meme\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n41 minutes ago, selfish_meme said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave you got a Patreon page or something LGG?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#1155cc;\u0022\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.patreon.com/linuxgurugamer\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.patreon.com/linuxgurugamer\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"selfish_meme","CreatedById":125899,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-22T11:38:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223099605\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002233124\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221498128839\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n42 minutes ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#1155cc;\u0022\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.patreon.com/linuxgurugamer\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.patreon.com/linuxgurugamer\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbah, what was I thinking Patreon annoys me, have you got a \u00A0wallet? Ethereum, bitcoin etc?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"strudo76","CreatedById":175831,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-30T07:15:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey there\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan someone help me understand how this works?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot8.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i806.photobucket.com/albums/yy345/strudo76/screenshot8.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have one \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thruster only, with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E-BA set to display attitude. I don\u0027t understand where the straight red arrow comes from, or how to get rid of it. I know the green arrow represents the translation movement, and the red circle represents how fast the rotation will occur. The straight red arrow represents the torque force on the craft, but I don\u0027t know where it comes from or how to remove it. The only way I can seem to remove it completely is to set put the thruster at the centre of mass, which then removes the rotation as well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd then this image\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot9.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i806.photobucket.com/albums/yy345/strudo76/screenshot9.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have two equal thrusters, both firing in the same direction, and yet there is a net torque force in one direction that I don\u0027t understand where it comes from.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-30T07:21:25Z\u0022 title=\u002206/30/2017 07:21  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 30, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by strudo76\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EAdditional picture\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"capi3101","CreatedById":59027,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-30T16:16:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223107064\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002233124\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221498806913\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022175831\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022strudo76\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, strudo76 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey there\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan someone help me understand how this works?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0026lt;snip\u0026gt;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll give it a try. TL:DR is that the red arrow is your torque \u003Cem\u003Evector\u003C/em\u003E; the way you get it go away entirely is either by putting your thruster on your center of mass OR by putting an equal amount of counter-force at a distance exactly as far away from the center of mass as your initial thruster.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThere are three components to torque - the amount of force applied (which depends on the output of your thrusters), the length of the lever arm (i.e. how far the thruster is from the center of mass, which is going to be your fulcrum), and the angle between them. In this case, your force vector is going to be at a right angle to the lever arm - sine of ninety degrees is 1, so that factors out of consideration. So, the magnitude of your torque in a given axis is going to equal the thrust times the distance to the center of mass. The direction of the torque vector can be determined by using the right hand grip rule: if the fingers of the right hand are curled from the direction of the lever arm to the direction of the force, then the thumb points in the direction of the torque. What \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E Build aid is doing when it\u0027s telling you the total torque on a single axis is that it\u0027s calculating the torques for all thrusters that will affect that axis - the amount of force they provide, how far away they are from the selected \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E, and what angle they are to the axis. It then adds those up and gives you the result.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf you\u0027re really wanting to use \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters for rotation with a craft like the one you\u0027ve pictured, I\u0027d start by putting a series of thrusters at the top - up by the parachute. These won\u0027t be at a ninety degree angle to the lever arm, and so the net torque they\u0027d produce will be less than those you could put at the same distance from the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E on the bottom. Myself, I use \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters for docking, which is a procedure where you want as little torque produced when you fire a thruster as you can possibly manage (so therefore I put them around the center of mass)\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Torque\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Torque\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0- mandatory wikipedia link on the topic of torque.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t think I\u0027ve really explained this particularly well; hopefully at least some of this is helpful.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kcs123","CreatedById":127158,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-30T18:14:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFew pages back and couple of months ago, I tried to explain it to other user:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/33124-12-rcs-build-aid-v091/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=2880047\u0026amp;embedComment=2880047\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"strudo76","CreatedById":175831,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-01T13:32:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223107367\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002233124\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221498839402\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002259027\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022capi3101\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 hours ago, capi3101 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll give it a try. TL:DR is that the red arrow is your torque \u003Cem\u003Evector\u003C/em\u003E; the way you get it go away entirely is either by putting your thruster on your center of mass OR by putting an equal amount of counter-force at a distance exactly as far away from the center of mass as your initial thruster.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t think I\u0027ve really explained this particularly well; hopefully at least some of this is helpful.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223107472\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002233124\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221498846464\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127158\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kcs123\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 hours ago, kcs123 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFew pages back and couple of months ago, I tried to explain it to other user:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/33124-12-rcs-build-aid-v091/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=2880047\u0026amp;embedComment=2880047\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBoth very helpful posts, thank you. I guess my only remaining question is will the craft translate in the direction of\u00A0the torque vector while I\u0027m rotating?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kcs123","CreatedById":127158,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-01T18:19:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223108189\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002233124\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221498915927\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022175831\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022strudo76\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, strudo76 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBoth very helpful posts, thank you. I guess my only remaining question is will the craft translate in the direction of\u00A0the torque vector while I\u0027m rotating?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGame will always try to translate craft, meaning, it will turn on those \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E ports that have at least some thrust(force) that will push craft (translate) it in desired direction. While doing this, depending on position of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E ports that try to translate craft in desired direction you will get also unwanted rotation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen you get unwanted rotation, game will again try to engage \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E ports that should provide oposite force that cancel rotation. Often, those ports provide oposite force from direction of desired translation, therefore also waste of fuel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKeeping that in mind, what you want in craft design process, to minimize rotation, idealy it should be zero, when you try to translate craft in any of desired direction. That is where this mod kicks in, giving you visual feedback, how much of rotation you get for any of translation direction. By placing \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E on symetrical distance from \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E, or changing thrust maximum for each \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E port, you can achieve zero rotation or near zero rotation for all translation direction.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m saying near zero rotation, because you have design craft very carefuly in a way that \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E does not shift at all when you drain fuel and other resources. Also, having zero rotation for any given translation, does not mean that you would not rotate craft with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E at all. It yust mean you didn\u0027t waste resources on rotation that you does not want.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"blowfish","CreatedById":119688,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-01T18:41:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223108189\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002233124\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221498915927\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022175831\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022strudo76\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, strudo76 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBoth very helpful posts, thank you. I guess my only remaining question is will the craft translate in the direction of\u00A0the torque vector while I\u0027m rotating?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt will not translate in the direction of the torque vector. \u00A0The torque vector could just as easily point in the opposite direction, the only reason it doesn\u0027t is mathematical convention.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nick88","CreatedById":150645,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-16T13:22:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor anyone having problems with identifying the direction the ship will turn when looking at the torque vector, use the \u0022right hand rule\u0022 (or right thumb rule). Make a fist with right hand\u00A0with thumb popping out, now, if you put the fist\u00A0in such a way that the thumb is pointing in the same direction as the torque vector (red arrow), the \u0027curl\u0027 of the\u00A0other 4 fingers represents the direction in which the ship rotates. Check this more info and images:\u003Ca href=\u0022http://hyperphysics.phy-astr.gsu.edu/hbase/tord.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ERight Hand Rule\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGreat mod, this should be stock IMHO. It becomes frustratingly hard trying to balance \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E and engine torque without this. Thanks \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/67965-m4v/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002267965\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/67965-m4v/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@m4v\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0for the mod and \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022129964\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@linuxgurugamer\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0for the fixes!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Emrys","CreatedById":179954,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-19T10:47:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can\u0027t use \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E Build Aid right now i havent play ksp for a while downloaded it recently and take x science engineer redux and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003Ercs\u003C/abbr\u003E build aid but i couldn\u0027t download it from \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003Eckan\u003C/abbr\u003E i download it from here first 1.2 version icon appeared on screen but when i click it nothing happend than i download 9.1.2 version at the last page but know cant even see icon in hangar\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MaverickSawyer","CreatedById":11952,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-19T16:08:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022129964\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@linuxgurugamer\u003C/a\u003E is, thankfully, running a continuation project that has released a 1.3 compatible version.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Emrys","CreatedById":179954,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-26T09:09:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223125599\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002233124\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221500480510\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002211952\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MaverickSawyer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 19.07.2017 at 7:08 PM, MaverickSawyer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022129964\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@linuxgurugamer\u003C/a\u003E is, thankfully, running a continuation project that has released a 1.3 compatible version.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nis it out?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ThreePounds","CreatedById":116058,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-26T14:51:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223131508\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002233124\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221501060182\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022179954\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Emrys\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Emrys said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nis it out?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes. Check on his guthub.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-07-26T14:51:25Z\u0022 title=\u002207/26/2017 02:51  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 26, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Three_Pounds\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-26T14:53:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223131651\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002233124\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221501080668\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022116058\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Three_Pounds\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Three_Pounds said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes. Check on his guthub.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWould be nice if you linked it:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/linuxgurugamer/RCSBuildAid/releases\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/linuxgurugamer/RCSBuildAid/releases\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kobymaru","CreatedById":107372,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-26T15:32:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223131654\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002233124\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221501080785\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n38 minutes ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWould be nice if you linked it:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/linuxgurugamer/RCSBuildAid/releases\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/linuxgurugamer/RCSBuildAid/releases\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder if it\u0027s possible to add a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E source for all of your stuff. Would be wonderful if we could just plop that into \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E and update to your unofficial rebuilds.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Brigadier","CreatedById":147109,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-27T00:15:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223131687\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002233124\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221501083140\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107372\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kobymaru\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Kobymaru said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder if it\u0027s possible to add a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E source for all of your stuff. Would be wonderful if we could just plop that into \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E and update to your unofficial rebuilds.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAFAIK, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E doesn\u0027t do betas, which is how this unofficial update is characterized on GitHub.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"desepticon","CreatedById":84561,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-27T02:52:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223132057\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002233124\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221501114556\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022147109\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Brigadier\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Brigadier said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAFAIK, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E doesn\u0027t do betas, which is how this unofficial update is characterized on GitHub.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually you can setup \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E to install a DEV version. I do this with mechjeb. You\u0027d have to add a special dev repo for your stuff to the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E github though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E you add a line to your setting to add a metadata repo. Currently SCANsat, Trajectories, Mechjeb, and RemoteTech have this option.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-27T15:38:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s the new repo in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E which I\u0027m avoiding, too much chance of confusion\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kobymaru","CreatedById":107372,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-27T15:43:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223132551\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002233124\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221501169893\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s the new repo in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E which I\u0027m avoiding, too much chance of confusion\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell it shouldn\u0027t be on by default, but it would be very helpful for those who know what they are doing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}